<TITLE> Atletico Madrid's Aguirre says steps down as coach </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, Feb 3 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Javier Aguirre said on Tuesday he had stepped down as coach of Atletico Madrid after agreeing with club president Enrique Cerezo to end his contract. "We have reached a good agreement," Mexican Aguirre told Cadena Ser radio. "I am the first to understand that I am a fundamental part of the problem the team finds itself in." Atletico have not won a match this year and slipped to seventh in the standings after a 2-1 home defeat by Real Valladolid in the Primera Liga on Sunday. Spanish media reported on Monday that Aguirre would be replaced at the club by Abel Resino, a former Atletico goalkeeper who is coach of second division Castellon
